cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the task of unsupervised video-to-video translation, which involves generating videos in a target domain from videos in a source domain without any paired training examples. This task is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM) as it involves learning a mapping between two domains. The paper also mentions the use of adversarial constraints and cycle consistency, which are common techniques in generative models and deep learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with motion estimation and spatio-temporal structures in videos, which are relevant to graphics (cs.GR).
